 for bestpractices and # Admin Dashboard

## Overview
Create a feature-rich Admin Dashboard for StudySpark that enables administrators to manage users, moderate content, manage subscription plans, and view analytics/reporting. The dashboard should be secure, responsive, and accessible, with a polished UI that matches the project's design system: soft pastels, rounded components, friendly iconography, and data-focused visualizations. Ensure runtime safety by guarding against null/undefined values for all data operations, initialize state with proper defaults, and validate all API responses.

## Page Description (Full Detail)
The Admin Dashboard page is the control center for system administration and operational visibility. It consolidates four core domains into a single, tabbed/sectioned interface:

- User Management
  - Display a searchable, sortable, and paginated table of users with details (name, email, role, status, createdAt, lastActive).
  - Actions per user: suspend/reactivate, impersonate, send message, edit profile, reset password, and delete (soft-delete if applicable).
  - Bulk actions: select multiple users to suspend, delete, or assign roles.
  - Validation and safety: confirm destructive actions; preserve audit logs; respect role-based access controls.

- Content Moderation
  - Present a queue of flagged content items (e.g., studies, materials) with moderator notes, flag reasons, and user associations.
  - Moderator actions: approve, ban, or request changes; attach notes; escalate to higher moderation tier if needed.
  - Filters: by flag type, content type, date range, status (pending/reviewed/approved/ban).
  - Moderation workflow state management and history.

- Subscription Plans
  - CRUD interface for plans, pricing tiers, features, quotas, trial periods, and localization.
  - Coupon and promotion management with validity windows, usage limits, and eligibility rules.
  - Vision for analytics around ARPU, churn, MAU-driven revenue, and plan adoption rates.
  - Import/export of plan data (CSV/JSON) for admin operations.

- Analytics & Reporting
  - KPI dashboard with MAU, Monthly Recurring Revenue (MRR), churn, active subscriptions, creation volume, and system health indicators.
  - Time-series charts, cohort analysis, top funnels, and exportable reports (PDF/CSV).
  - Real-time or near-real-time data refresh where feasible; provide date range selectors and quick filters (last 7/30/90 days, YoY, etc.).
  - Data export as downloadable reports; ensure correct formatting and data validation.

Visual guidance:
- Consistent with the provided visual style: pastel peach, muted lavender, bright tangerine, deep violet accents; rounded cards; soft shadows; accessible typography and spacing.
- Data visualization should be clear and non-intrusive with minimal gridlines, pastel fills, and rounded bars for charts.
- Each major section should feel distinct with appropriate card backgrounds, borders, and hover/active states.

## Components to Build
- AdminLayout
  - Top bar with avatar, progress indicators, quick actions.
  - Left navigation or tabbed navigation with sections: Users, Moderation, Plans, Analytics.
- UserManagementPanel
  - Search bar with debounced input, filters, and sort controls.
  - UserTable: columns for ID, name, email, role, status, createdAt, lastActive, actions.
  - BulkActionsBar: select all, bulk suspend/delete/role changes, export.
  - Modals: ConfirmDialog, MessageUserDrawer, EditUserModal, SuspendUserModal.
- ModerationPanel
